      <body>The automatic message formed by ActiveRecord::RecordInvalid is 

@@@ ruby
&quot;Validation failed: #{@record.errors.full_messages.join(&quot;, &quot;)}&quot;
@@@

It should be changed so that it is available for translation.  Something like:

@@@ ruby
I18n.t('activerecord.errors.validation_failed', :full_messages =&gt; @record.errors.full_messages.join(I18n.t('support.array.words_connector'))
@@@</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The automatic message formed by ActiveRecord::RecordInvalid
is&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=
&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&quot;Validation failed: #{@record.errors.full_messages.join(&quot;, &quot;)}&quot;&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It should be changed so that it is available for translation.
Something like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=
&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;I18n.t('activerecord.errors.validation_failed', :full_messages =&amp;gt; @record.errors.full_messages.join(I18n.t('support.array.words_connector'))&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
